{"componentChunkName":"component---src-views-book-page-index-tsx","path":"/books/the-secret-barrister-the-secret-barrister/","result":{"data":{"book":{"id":"4722f265-f0d1-5935-b2f1-86a5bd37ca69-book","slug":"/books/the-secret-barrister-the-secret-barrister/","links":{"long":{"gr":"https://www.goodreads.com/search?query=9781509841141","amzn":"https://www.amazon.co.uk/dp/1509841148?tag=thcdex-21","bd":"https://bookdepository.com/search?searchTerm=9781509841141&a_id=char"}},"title":"The Secret Barrister","subtitle":null,"summary":"You may not wish to think about it, but one day you or someone you love will almost certainly appear in a criminal courtroom. You might be a juror, a victim, a witness or perhaps through no fault of your own a defendant. Whatever your role, you d expect a fair trial. I'm a barrister. I work in the criminal justice system, and every day I see how fairness is not guaranteed. Too often the system fails those it is meant to protect. The innocent are wronged and the guilty allowed to walk free. I want to share some stories from my daily life to show you how the system is broken, who broke it and why we should start caring before it s too late.\n","tags":["type-non-fiction","sub-politics","form-paperback","book-club"],"readDates":[["2019-05-15T00:00:00.000Z","2019-05-19T00:00:00.000Z"]],"rating7":6,"rating5":5,"pageCount":320,"dateRated":"2019-05-19T00:00:00.000Z","dateBookPublished":"2018-03-22T00:00:00.000Z","dateReviewed":"2019-05-19T00:00:00.000Z","dateLastRead":"2019-05-19T00:00:00.000Z","author":"The Secret Barrister","publisher":"Pan Books","bookHeight":198,"series":null,"image":{"id":"562b62de-0998-518e-935e-fd6f9e557d6d","childImageSharp":{"id":"12e22be7-ab17-5755-beed-ee8c6d22a265","h200":{"width":132,"height":200,"src":"/static/3cc8981e5fccce1073dfe4d4220895fd/b3dc8/cover.jpg","srcSet":"/static/3cc8981e5fccce1073dfe4d4220895fd/b3dc8/cover.jpg 1x,\n/static/3cc8981e5fccce1073dfe4d4220895fd/02d26/cover.jpg 1.5x,\n/static/3cc8981e5fccce1073dfe4d4220895fd/a98b0/cover.jpg 2x"},"h300":{"width":198,"height":300,"src":"/static/3cc8981e5fccce1073dfe4d4220895fd/02d26/cover.jpg","srcSet":"/static/3cc8981e5fccce1073dfe4d4220895fd/02d26/cover.jpg 1x,\n/static/3cc8981e5fccce1073dfe4d4220895fd/f2a7d/cover.jpg 1.5x,\n/static/3cc8981e5fccce1073dfe4d4220895fd/e49df/cover.jpg 2x"},"h400":{"width":264,"height":400,"src":"/static/3cc8981e5fccce1073dfe4d4220895fd/a98b0/cover.jpg","srcSet":"/static/3cc8981e5fccce1073dfe4d4220895fd/a98b0/cover.jpg 1x,\n/static/3cc8981e5fccce1073dfe4d4220895fd/e49df/cover.jpg 1.5x,\n/static/3cc8981e5fccce1073dfe4d4220895fd/2d2bf/cover.jpg 2x"}},"colors":{"vibrant":"#F4E45E","darkVibrant":"#62522A","lightVibrant":"#EDD558","muted":"#9C8E5A","darkMuted":"#5C4435","lightMuted":"#C4A699"}},"html":"<p>This book is astonishing. I am now completely terrified of having any involvement in our criminal justice system as it currently stands. The author argues convincingly that our (England+Wales’) two-tiered court system and adversarial trial setup should result in the utmost justice for both defendants and complainants, but severe underfunding over the last two decades has turned it into a farce.</p>\n<p>I am not a big lefty, politically I’m much more inclined to a small state, but I truly believe that a reliable justice system should be the cornerstone of any government. There is a limp handshake in this social contract, and my eyes are now acutely open to it.</p>","relatedBooks":[{"id":"5f84b5e3-4546-5d55-8f86-9b2765de8817-book","slug":"/books/the-silk-roads-peter-frankopan/","title":"The Silk Roads","author":"Peter Frankopan","rating7":3,"dateReviewed":null,"bookHeight":198,"image":{"id":"2fbe8eb5-ff16-5e85-b4d4-3c7745345442","childImageSharp":{"id":"9b1a2d32-ab67-5585-9656-c72e4d84eb74","h150":{"width":99,"height":150,"src":"/static/77562ff2b6fb0a0f873aed4ad28032fc/56830/cover.jpg","srcSet":"/static/77562ff2b6fb0a0f873aed4ad28032fc/56830/cover.jpg 1x,\n/static/77562ff2b6fb0a0f873aed4ad28032fc/c66